# Delivery Rider — Configuration Reference
# This app is now plain HTML/CSS/JS — no build step required.
# Configuration is done directly in app.js.

# ── app.js variables ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# API_BASE  (line ~3 in app.js)
#   The base URL of the MediFlow backend.
#   Default: 'https://mediflow-backend-z29j.onrender.com'
#
# USE_MOCK  (line ~8 in app.js)
#   Set to `true`  → runs entirely with local sample data, no backend needed.
#   Set to `false` → calls the real API at API_BASE.
#   The MOCK_DISPATCHES array (below in app.js) holds the sample data and can
#   be deleted when connecting to a real backend.

# ── Running locally ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   Open index.html directly in a browser, or serve with any static server:
#     npx serve .          (Node)
#     python3 -m http.server 8080   (Python)
#
# ── Deploying to GitHub Pages ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   The GitHub Actions workflow (.github/workflows/deploy.yml) deploys the
#   root of the repository directly to GitHub Pages on every push to main.
#   No build step is needed.
